								BTPHub: A Startup and App for Neighborhoods
							</div>
							<div class="project-subtitle" style={{borderBottom: '1px solid rgb(116, 113, 113)', paddingBottom: '12px'}}>
								<span>
									<i class="fa-regular fa-hand-pointer" style={{color: '#060021', fontWeight: '500'}}></i>
								</span>
								Visit BTPHub Pilot:<a href="https://qa.btphub.com/" target="_blank"><b>Enter Website</b></a>
							</div>

							<div class="project-paragraph" style={{color: 'rgb(50, 47, 47)'}}>
								<b>
									Tools used: Vue.js, Javascript, HTML, CSS, Figma, C# for .NET Core, .NET Aspire, Postman API Platform, SendGrid API, Azure SQL
								</b>
							</div>
							<div class="project-paragraph" style={{color: 'rgb(0, 0, 0)'}}>
								<div style={{color: 'rgb(77, 7, 7)'}}><u><b>Development Highlights: </b></u></div>
								<ul class="highlight-list">
									<li><b style={{color: 'rgb(177, 24, 24)'}}><i class="fa-solid fa-star" style={{marginRight: '3px', color: '#f6c832'}}></i> 40+</b> neighborhoods registered pre-release.</li>
									<li><b style={{color: 'rgb(177, 24, 24)'}}>35k+</b> lines of code written across frontend, backend, and middleware (according to VSCode).</li>
									<li><b style={{color: 'rgb(177, 24, 24)'}}>100+</b> components and pages created across frontend web app.</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							
							<div class="project-paragraph" style={{marginTop: '15px'}}>
								BTPHub is a tech startup I co-founded focused on connecting families with trusted childcare and senior care providers within their local communities. 
								Our application makes it easy to find and schedule care, fostering stronger neighborhood connections.
								The app enables providers, such as babysitters and petsitters, to share their availability and accept service requests, while customers can easily find trusted providers nearby and manage all their bookings. 
								The app’s neighborhood-centered design ensures a trusted, community-based experience for all users.
							</div>
							<div class="project-paragraph">
								As CTO, our team uses tools like SQL databases, APIs, and JavaScript frameworks (e.g., Vue) to create a smooth and reliable user experience. 
								BTPHub aims to make care more accessible and convenient for everyone.
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="project-image" >
							<img src={btpHubPic.src} alt="" class="project-pic" style={{background: 'white'}}/>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="portfolio-project">
						<div class="project-text">
							<div class="project-title">
								BNT Foundation Website
							</div>
							<div class="project-subtitle" style={{borderBottom: '1px solid rgb(116, 113, 113)', paddingBottom: '12px'}}>
								<span>
									<i class="fa-regular fa-hand-pointer"></i>
								</span>
								Visit BNT Foundation Website:<a href="https://www.bntllc.co/foundation" target="_blank"><b>Enter Website</b></a>
							</div>
							
							<div class="project-paragraph" style={{color: 'rgb(50, 47, 47)'}}>
								<b>
									Tools used: NextJS, React, Javascript, Three.js, HTML, CSS, REST APIs
								</b>
							</div>
							
							<div class="project-paragraph" style={{marginTop: '15px'}}>
								BNT Foundation is the non-profit I co-founded. We are a team with over 20 volunteers dedicated to supporting communities in need. 
								Some of our initiatives include partnering with the Harvard China Fund and Jianghao to donate specialized bras to breast cancer patients, and helping sponsor and organize community events like Johns Creek's New Years Gala.
							</div>
							<div class="project-paragraph">
								I designed and built the BNT Foundation website from scratch using NextJS, focusing on creating a clear, user-friendly design.
								The website features interactive features, including 3D hero sections that enable users to explore dynamic visuals. Developing these features involved learning fundamental 3D modeling and WebGL techniques using Spline.
								I also utilized REST APIs from SendGrid and Paypal to develop key user interaction features in the site. At the core, the website includes detailed information about what we've done at BNT Foundation.
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="project-image" >
							<img src={bntPic.src} alt="" class="project-pic" style={{background: 'white'}} />
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<Home client:only="react"/>

			<div class="footer">
				<div class="footer-item">
					Alexander Xu
				</div>
				<div class="footer-item">
					<a href="mailto: xualex008@gmail.com">Contact</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
	</div>
